## Hints & warnings
- weave/session/ is INTENTIONALLY kept as a deprecation shim (only __init__.py,
  emits DeprecationWarning, re-exports). weave/conversation/_deprecated.py holds the
  session-named aliases (Session, start_session, end_session, log_session,
  get_current_session) that forward to conversation equivalents and translate
  session_id/session_name -> conversation_id/conversation_name. weave/__init__.py
  exposes BOTH the canonical conversation names AND the deprecated session aliases at
  top level. tests/conversation/test_deprecation.py exercises this. DO NOT "finish
  the rename" by deleting these — they are the back-compat surface.
- pyproject.toml keeps BOTH weave.session and weave.conversation in the 3
  [[tool.importlinter.contracts]] forbidden-module lists — correct, both packages
  physically ship (conversation=canonical, session=shim).
- Unrelated "session" usage left untouched (NOT part of the SDK rename): Sentry
  sessions (telemetry/trace_sentry.py, weave_init end_session), AWS session tokens
  (file_storage*), Kafka session.timeout, MCP ClientSession (fastmcp), OpenAI-realtime
  session concept (integrations/openai_realtime/*), Claude Agent SDK session_id
  (mapped to our conversation_id in otel_integration.py), Google ADK runner
  session_id, pytest session-scope fixtures, nox.session, ClickHouse
  autogenerate_session_id. The trace_server attribute layer (semconv.py CONVERSATION_ID
  description "Conversation or session ID"; schema.py comment "conversation / session")
  already used conversation naming pre-PR and accurately documents that the field also
  receives upstream session IDs — left as-is.

